Our criminal justice system must prioritize rehabilitation, not retribution.

Abusive treatment at federal correctional facilities has no place in our justice system.

@ChuckGrassley, @Sen_JoeManchin, @SenCapito, and I are urging DOJ and BOP to investigate FCC Hazelton.

Big day: We’re voting on Supreme Court ethics reform legislation in the Senate Judiciary Committee.

@SenWhitehouse and I are previewing the vote on @CNNThisMorning and @MSNBC @Morning_Joe during the 8:00 hour this morning.

Tune in!

MAGA House Republicans passed a NDAA that would abandon our service members and our allies.

They want to eliminate access to reproductive health care for service members and undermine climate action initiatives amid record-breaking heat.

@SenateDems won't let it happen.

Great to meet young activists with @DesignItForUs this afternoon.

@JudiciaryDems are on a mission to protect kids online. These youth advocates have experienced the ills of social media firsthand.

I’m grateful for their efforts, turning their experience into change.

Today’s a big day: our bipartisan INFORM Consumers Act goes into effect!

Our bill will combat scammers flooding the internet with stolen or counterfeit products, from cosmetics to kids’ toys.

@SenBillCassidy, thanks for the great teamwork getting our bill signed into law.

A big initiative for @JudiciaryDems this year: stopping the exploitation of kids online.

Our mission requires all-hands-on-deck.

@LindseyGrahamSC and I just introduced a bill to reauthorize the Missing Children’s Assistance Act, supporting this work for years to come.

In February, this bombshell New York Times report exposed widespread exploitation of migrant children.

It was a call to action. We have a moral and legal responsibility to protect them.

@JudiciaryDems is holding a hearing on it now.

I agree with @Surgeon_General’s warning: social media is exacerbating the youth mental health crisis.

Big Tech is taking a page out of Big Tobacco’s playbook, hooking our kids on social media.

@JudiciaryDems are pushing back – and prioritizing kids.

A big morning in the Senate Judiciary Committee.

@JudiciaryDems are holding the first Congressional hearing of the year on reproductive rights.

We will fight for the rights of millions of women today – and call out the hypocrisy of anti-abortion extremists.
